title: Darwin's Doubt and Intelligent Design - Collection 4
description:
Darwin's Doubt and Intelligent Design - Collection 4:

We have 20 titles here:

-  Aczel - Why Science Does Not Disprove God (2014)

-  Bickerton - Adam's Tongue; How Humans Made Language, How Language Made Humans (2009)

-  Bowler - Monkey Trials and Gorilla Sermons; Evolution and Christianity from Darwin to Intelligent Design (2007)

-  Burton - A Skeptic's Guide to the Mind; What Neuroscience Can and Cannot Tell Us About Ourselves (2013)

-  Fortey - Horseshoe Crabs and Velvet Worms; the Story of the Animals and Plants That Time Has Left Behind (2011)

-  Goodman - Creation and Evolution (2010)

-  Johnston - Evolution; Fact or Fable (2002)

-  Mithen - The Prehistory of the Mind; a Search for the Origins of Art, Religion and Science (1996)

-  Richards - The Species Problem; a Philosophical Analysis (2010)

-  Seckbach & Gordon (Eds.) - Divine Action and Natural Selection; Science, Faith and Evolution (2009)

-  Sheiman - An Atheist Defends Religion (2009)

-  Thaxton et al - The Mystery of Life's Origin; Reassessing Current Theories (1992)

-  Wade - A Troublesome Inheritance; Genes, Race and Human History (2014)

-  Wells - Icons of Evolution, Science or Myth; Why Much of What We Teach about Evolution Is Wrong (2000)

-  Wells - The Myth of Junk DNA (2011)

-  Werner - Evolution; the Grand Experiment, 2e (2014)

-  Yahya - Atlas of Creation, part 1, 12e (2007)

-  Yahya - Atlas of Creation, part 3, 12e (2007)
